LIBRARY SERVICES TO THE HANDICAPPED PERSONS IN THE DEVELOPING NATIONS.

ARGUES THAT LIBRARIES FOR THE HANDICAPPED AND THE DISADVANTAGED SHOULD HAVE
HIGH PRIORITY IN EVERY COUNTRY'S LIBRARY PROVISION. DISCUSSES WAYS IN WHICH
LIBRARIES IN DEVELOPING COUNTRIES COULD EXTEND THEIR SERVICES TO THE BLIND AND
TO PEOPLE CONFINED IN HOSPITALS AND PRISONS.
